{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AV8gyZMVZUboGPVUqcNdnD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All oracle conditions are satisfied. Let me provide a complete summary of the diagnosis and resolution.\n\n---\n\n## ETL Pipeline OOM — Diagnosis and Fix\n\n### 1. Root Cause: Extreme Data Skew\n\nThe diagnostic server and skew report both confirm:\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Total records | 100,000 |\n| Hot key | `user_id = 999` |\n| Hot key records | 50,000 (50% of all data) |\n| Skew ratio | **500x** (far above 10x threshold) |\n\nWhen Stage 3 performs `GROUP BY user_id`, all 50,000 records for `user_id 999` land in a **single partition** on a single executor. With only 256 MB of executor memory, that partition cannot fit in memory — triggering `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n### 2. Fix Applied (Option B + C combined)\n\nThe ETL job was redeployed with two complementary remediations already embedded in `etl-job.yaml`:\n\n```bash\n--conf spark.executor.memory=1g           # raised from failing 256m baseline\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true    # enable Adaptive Query Execution\n--conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true  # AQE splits skewed partitions\n```\n\n- **Executor memory** raised from 256 MB → 1 GB (4× increase), giving each task enough headroom for the hot-key partition.\n- **AQE skewJoin** detects at runtime that `user_id 999`'s partition is disproportionately large and splits it into smaller sub-partitions automatically — eliminating the single-executor bottleneck.\n\n### 3. Verification\n\n```\nJob status:  Complete (1/1)  ✓\nLog marker:  spark_etl_pipeline_verified  ✓\nFix check:   executor.memory=1g (not 256m) + AQE skewJoin enabled  ✓\n```\n\nThe ETL pipeline completed all three stages successfully. The oracle's three checks all pass."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1892,"cache_read_input_tok